  "prompt": "What software do Ghibli / Japanese studios use to create anime?",
  "response": "Japanese anime studios, including Studio Ghibli, use a variety of software tools to create their animations. Some commonly used software in the industry includes:\n\n1. **RETAS Studio**: This is one of the most widely used tools in the Japanese anime industry. It offers a suite of tools including PaintMan for digital painting, TraceMan for digitizing hand-drawn sketches, and Stylos for 2D animation.\n\n2. **Toonz**: This software is used extensively for 2D animation and has been customized for specific studios like Studio Ghibli. \"Toonz Ghibli Edition\" is a version tailored to their needs.\n\n3. **Adobe Photoshop**: Often used for background artwork and texturing, Photoshop is a staple for many artists.\n\n4. **Adobe After Effects**: This software is commonly used for adding special effects, compositing, and post-production work.\n\n5. **CLIP STUDIO PAINT**: A popular tool for drawing and painting, CLIP Studio Paint is used for creating detailed character designs and backgrounds.\n\n6. **TVPaint Animation**: This is another professional-grade software used for 2D animation, offering extensive features for frame-by-frame animation.\n\nDifferent studios may also have their preferred or proprietary software tailored to their unique workflows and styles. Additionally, traditional techniques, such as hand-drawn animation, remain an essential part of the process in many studios.",
